  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sensory and motor cueing have been demonstrated as useful ambulation training techniques for
      Parkinson's disease (PD). This study is aimed to evaluate the effectiveness of treadmill
      training program with music cueing for mild to moderate PD patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
